                            There are multiple statistics and not just what Ashok Malik has mentioned in the article about the contribution Agriculture makes to our national income versus the people dependent on them. Agriculture's contribution to India's national income is not more than 15% where as 50-50% of our population are dependent on it. All over the world, Developed nations have no more than 8-10% of their national income contributed by Agriculture. And all Developed countries, not more than 10% of its population is dependent on Agriculture. Even china has moved massive number of its people out of Agriculture to other productive areas. Its a myth that moving people and reducing agriculture areas will reduce food production. US with less than 5% of population on Agriculture produces more than India. Agriculture Productivity has to be improved by using modern technology and not by having more poor people doing it. <br/><br/>
